00:00:19.249 --> 00:00:23.750
THE NEST

3
00:02:42.700 --> 00:02:44.660
One. two. three and...

4
00:07:02.340 --> 00:07:04.060
With the king. eh?

5
00:07:16.460 --> 00:07:18.920
I see you coming.

6
00:07:20.580 --> 00:07:23.020
But I will not fall into your trap.

7
00:07:30.650 --> 00:07:33.000
How about a knight. hum?

8
00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:37.240
For now. check.

9
00:07:46.610 --> 00:07:48.270
Who are you?

10
00:07:49.450 --> 00:07:51.960
How many times should I tell you
not to bother me when I'm working?!

11
00:07:52.161 --> 00:07:53.961
And close the door.
we are not in the stables.

12
00:07:54.030 --> 00:07:56.070
- We are out of milk.
- It is of no importance to me.

13
00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:58.520
You should think of many things.

14
00:07:58.721 --> 00:08:00.521
And above all.
about keeping the house as God intended.

15
00:08:00.860 --> 00:08:02.940
- If only signora was alive...
- Never speak about signora.

16
00:08:03.130 --> 00:08:06.190
- And dinner. How about the dinner?
- Not now.

17
00:08:06.900 --> 00:08:09.380
- Go away. out. out.
- Go away. go away...

18
00:08:09.870 --> 00:08:14.550
Someday i will be gone forever
and you will stay alone.

19
00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:23.470
You see?

20
00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:27.340
No peace even in your own home.

21
00:08:33.640 --> 00:08:34.850
Oh. well.

22
00:08:37.110 --> 00:08:39.930
Let me see what you are up to.

23
00:08:49.660 --> 00:08:51.260
Can't you think of anything better?

24
00:08:56.550 --> 00:08:57.360
Checkmate.

25
00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:20.710
The goldfinch feather
will take you to the great tree. G.

26
00:10:00.180 --> 00:10:05.130
The jay feather
will lead you down the stream. G.

27
00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:51.290
?

28
00:10:51.490 --> 00:10:56.690
?

29
00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:28.800
The feather of the hawk
will take you to tower. G.

30
00:11:32.520 --> 00:11:33.380
Take this.

31
00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:35.700
- What is it?
- Milk. honey and cognac.

32
00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.010
Where have you managed to get so wet?

33
00:11:40.130 --> 00:11:42.180
- In the River.
- In the river. in the river...

34
00:11:42.610 --> 00:11:44.670
- What were you doing in the river?
- It's not your business.

35
00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:47.400
- The boots won't get dry here.
- Well. take them away.

36
00:11:48.220 --> 00:11:49.450
Ok. I'll take them.

37
00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:53.100
- I wonder what got into you. At you age...
- And what should I do at my age?

38
00:11:53.410 --> 00:11:55.290
Look after the house
and drink a good wine.

39
00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:58.470
- You have nothing to do in the kitchen?
- Yes. signor.

40
00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:01.200
I always have something to do
in the kitchen.

41
00:12:03.180 --> 00:12:04.450
- Amparo?
- What?

42
00:12:05.760 --> 00:12:08.320
Do you know anyone in the town
who is fond of birds?

43
00:12:08.660 --> 00:12:11.240
- Are you going to sell the nests?
- No.

44
00:12:12.070 --> 00:12:15.070
- Gumer. she has a bird store.
- Gumer?

45
00:12:19.550 --> 00:12:21.260
- Shall I bring you an aspirin?
- No.

46
00:12:22.010 --> 00:12:26.860
- Ah! In the River...
- And make sure you close that door.

47
00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:53.500
The goldfinch feather
will take you to the great tree.

48
00:13:02.020 --> 00:13:07.020
The jay feather
will lead you down the stream.

49
00:13:16.390 --> 00:13:20.850
The feather of the hawk
will take you to tower.

50
00:13:30.460 --> 00:13:31.310
G.

51
00:13:35.380 --> 00:13:36.530
Cookies.

52
00:13:38.680 --> 00:13:40.860
- Cookies. lentils...
- Lentils.

53
00:13:42.020 --> 00:13:43.380
- Cod.
- Cod.

54
00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:47.820
- And the cornstarch.
- A cornstarch.

55
00:13:48.640 --> 00:13:51.340
- Is that all?
- Yes.

56
00:13:57.150 --> 00:13:57.970
Good morning.

57
00:13:58.210 --> 00:14:00.990
- Good morning. Don Alejandro.
- Good morning.

58
00:14:01.410 --> 00:14:03.610
- Good morning. how are you?
- Good morning.

59
00:14:04.310 --> 00:14:05.160
Fine.

60
00:14:05.410 --> 00:14:07.330
- Yeah. well.

61
00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.330
- The bill. Don...

62
00:14:09.331 --> 00:14:11.331
- Yes. write it down.
I'll pay you on Saturday.

63
00:14:11.590 --> 00:14:14.740
- Give my regards to signora.
- Thanks. Gumer.

64
00:14:16.020 --> 00:14:18.590
- Always at your service. Don Alejandro.
- Good morning.

65
00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:23.430
- What do you want?
- Well... nothing in particular.

66
00:14:23.700 --> 00:14:24.870
I don't know what I could suggest you.

67
00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:29.450
- Do you have bird food?
- For which birds?

68
00:14:30.800 --> 00:14:33.730
- Common ones.
- I have birdseed and ca�amones.

69
00:14:35.050 --> 00:14:37.030
- Give me half a kilo.

70
00:14:37.950 --> 00:14:38.800
Of what?

71
00:14:39.640 --> 00:14:41.470
- Birdseed.
- Birdseed.

72
00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:52.170
- Are you breeding them?
- No. my sister is breeding them.

73
00:14:53.070 --> 00:14:56.020
- I guess your sister
doesn't climb trees. right?

74
00:14:57.040 --> 00:14:58.580
- Never. never.

75
00:14:58.581 --> 00:15:00.581
- And is there someone else
who is interested in birds?

76
00:15:00.760 --> 00:15:02.510
No. my sister. just my sister.

77
00:15:02.950 --> 00:15:06.160
- Nobody else?
- Just my sister. I told you.

78
00:15:22.770 --> 00:15:26.150
- Hello. sorcerer.
- Hello. heretic.

79
00:15:27.120 --> 00:15:29.040
You don't look well.
no customers. eh?

80
00:15:41.090 --> 00:15:43.170
- You sell all this?

81
00:15:45.240 --> 00:15:46.720
Don't be in a rush to buy. eh.

82
00:15:49.670 --> 00:15:53.030
This is what you call
the odor of sanctity.

83
00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:57.560
"Offensive is not he who wants to.
but the one who's able to. "

84
00:15:59.820 --> 00:16:02.520
Pa. dear brother. pa.

85
00:16:05.760 --> 00:16:08.570
Here. the church has always loved gifts.

86
00:16:13.870 --> 00:16:16.910
It is the first time
you gave me something.

87
00:16:18.260 --> 00:16:19.620
They aren't poisoned?

88
00:16:22.370 --> 00:16:25.040
When are you going
to dress in civil clothes?

89
00:16:25.041 --> 00:16:27.041
Or when will you
shave off your mustache?

90
00:16:36.030 --> 00:16:39.060
Hey. bogey. I need your help.

91
00:16:40.920 --> 00:16:44.710
You. as well as being puny and cheat.

92
00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:46.630
have a reputation of a man

93
00:16:46.631 --> 00:16:48.631
with the knowledge
of handwriting and astronomy. right?

94
00:16:49.250 --> 00:16:52.170
Sciences more accurate than those
you studied in seminary.

95
00:16:55.910 --> 00:17:00.100
- That's pneumonia.
- That's shit.

96
00:17:03.060 --> 00:17:04.130
Well. can you help me or not?

97
00:17:06.880 --> 00:17:10.360
- Are you asking for a confession?
- No. you don't get it.

98
00:17:12.040 --> 00:17:13.010
Look at this.

99
00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:26.600
- Who wrote this?
- I have no idea.

100
00:17:27.890 --> 00:17:30.240
- A woman?
- I suppose.

101
00:17:30.890 --> 00:17:35.670
You are too old to have love affairs.

102
00:17:37.190 --> 00:17:40.420
- I'm not interested in the erotic aspect
of the question. I want to find out...

103
00:17:40.421 --> 00:17:41.421
- Okay. okay.

104
00:17:42.060 --> 00:17:45.240
What happens is that
you do not understand anything.

105
00:17:45.241 --> 00:17:47.241
You talk a lot and you know nothing.

106
00:17:51.810 --> 00:17:53.690
- What type of bird
is mentioned in the first letter?

107
00:17:53.691 --> 00:17:54.691
- The goldfinch.

108
00:17:55.420 --> 00:17:57.150
Well. I had an egg of goldfinch.

109
00:18:00.280 --> 00:18:04.200
This was written by a girl.
Probably very young.

110
00:18:04.410 --> 00:18:06.360
That's obvious. Anything else?

111
00:18:07.550 --> 00:18:09.960
A glutton and dirty.

112
00:18:10.350 --> 00:18:12.830
- How do you know?
- Stains of fat on the paper.

113
00:18:19.540 --> 00:18:24.700
Uneducated. but with a great deal
of natural wit.

114
00:18:25.560 --> 00:18:28.580
- So she won't come here?

115
00:18:32.190 --> 00:18:36.130
I would say.
with a great sense of humor.

116
00:18:38.410 --> 00:18:41.890
Authoritarian and stubborn...

117
00:18:43.910 --> 00:18:45.510
...sensitive...

118
00:18:48.810 --> 00:18:49.950
Passionate.

119
00:18:52.190 --> 00:18:53.060
And absorbing.

120
00:18:57.730 --> 00:19:02.500
The feather of the hawk
will take you to tower. G.

121
00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:05.040
The tower.

122
00:19:07.680 --> 00:19:08.850
Bell tower.

123
00:19:12.270 --> 00:19:17.300
Have you climbed a bell tower?
It's a thousand pesetas.

124
00:19:31.010 --> 00:19:35.830
Why me. Eladio?
Why. whoever it is. has noticed me?

125
00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:39.010
Because you're the biggest
fool of all fools.

126
00:19:39.650 --> 00:19:41.980
- I'm serious.
- Me too.

127
00:19:42.820 --> 00:19:44.530
Maybe she is laughing at me?

128
00:19:58.340 --> 00:20:00.480
- I found it!
- Where?

129
00:20:01.370 --> 00:20:02.100
Find it yourself.

130
00:20:02.630 --> 00:20:04.740
What a man.

131
00:20:07.640 --> 00:20:13.290
Cold. cold. warm... hot.

132
00:20:14.920 --> 00:20:21.500
Very hot... very hot.
Hot like in hell.

133
00:20:27.720 --> 00:20:32.480
Falcon feathers will take you
to performance. G.

134
00:20:34.740 --> 00:20:37.380
Listen. I don't like this game.
Alejandro.

135
00:20:37.870 --> 00:20:39.190
I do not have another. priest.

136
00:20:42.970 --> 00:20:46.530
Yeah. I should just
eat my soup and drink wine. right?

137
00:20:48.830 --> 00:20:49.930
...to the concert...

138
00:20:52.640 --> 00:20:56.570
Eladio. I'll give you two thousand
pesetas to buy candles.

139
00:20:58.070 --> 00:20:59.290
It is a personal matter.

140
00:21:02.150 --> 00:21:07.090
Falcon feathers
will take you to performance. G.

141
00:21:09.930 --> 00:21:11.540
- Auntie.
- Mmm?

142
00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:15.000
The school children
are rehearsing Macbeth.

143
00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:17.770
Macbeth?

144
00:21:21.300 --> 00:21:23.520
The Raven Himself Is Hoarse...

145
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:28.980
...announces the fatal entrance of
Duncan. Under my battlements.

146
00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:31.650
- Run to me.
- Pause.

147
00:21:31.980 --> 00:21:34.470
- The evil spirits that wait
on thoughts of murder.

148
00:21:34.471 --> 00:21:35.471
- Breath.

149
00:21:35.680 --> 00:21:37.740
- And fill me from the crown
to the toe top-full.

150
00:21:37.741 --> 00:21:38.741
- Breath.

151
00:21:39.220 --> 00:21:42.650
- Of direst cruelty! make thick my blood.
- Pause.

152
00:21:43.900 --> 00:21:49.310
Thick my blood. Stop up th'access
and passage to remorse.

153
00:21:50.100 --> 00:21:54.160
Goyita. don't exaggerate.
Try to speak calmly.

154
00:21:55.170 --> 00:21:58.070
Make a pause and take a breath.

155
00:21:59.140 --> 00:22:02.210
And think of Macbeth.
you're waiting for him.

156
00:22:03.060 --> 00:22:07.100
With intonation and rhythm.
And last verse. please. Come on.

157
00:22:08.350 --> 00:22:13.770
That no compunctious visitings
of nature Shake my fell purpose.

158
00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:18.950
Nor keep peace between
Th'effect and it.

159
00:22:20.660 --> 00:22:24.300
Come to my woman's breasts
and take my milk for gall.

160
00:22:25.730 --> 00:22:28.060
you murd'ring ministers.

161
00:22:30.170 --> 00:22:37.310
Come. thick night. and pall thee
in the dunnest smoke of hell.

162
00:22:40.480 --> 00:22:42.850
That my keen knife see not
the wound it makes.

163
00:22:43.920 --> 00:22:51.230
Nor heaven peep through the blanket
of the dark. To cry - Hold.

164
00:22:53.290 --> 00:22:54.040
...hold.

165
00:22:57.670 --> 00:22:58.470
Come in. Tonio.

166
00:23:04.760 --> 00:23:06.200
My dearest love.
Duncan comes here tonight.

167
00:23:08.900 --> 00:23:12.790
Goyita. Macbeth has arrived?
Goyita. what's wrong?

168
00:23:13.420 --> 00:23:14.740
Silence!

169
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:19.040
- Sorry. this is a rehearsal.
- Pardon me.

170
00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:22.620
The rehearsal is private.

171
00:23:24.910 --> 00:23:27.090
- Sorry again.
- Thank you.

172
00:23:54.820 --> 00:23:57.770
- Falcon feathers...
- will take you to performance.

173
00:23:58.420 --> 00:24:01.210
- You don't like music?
- I like it very much.

174
00:24:02.360 --> 00:24:04.530
- Whose egg was it?
- Jackdaw.

175
00:24:05.160 --> 00:24:07.580
You see. I thought
it was of goldfinch.

176
00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:14.010
- Where are you going Lady Macbeth?
- Home.

177
00:24:15.240 --> 00:24:17.070
- Can I join you?
- Okay.

178
00:24:20.430 --> 00:24:24.870
Glamis hath murderd sleep. and
therefore Cawdor shall sleep no more.

179
00:24:25.580 --> 00:24:27.680
Macbeth shall sleep no more!

180
00:24:31.420 --> 00:24:33.660
- Bless you.
- Thanks.

181
00:24:34.680 --> 00:24:35.610
Have you caught a cold?

182
00:24:39.080 --> 00:24:41.160
When I have cold.
I always end up with angina.

183
00:24:44.390 --> 00:24:46.970
- Did you have your tonsils operated?
- I don't remember.

184
00:24:48.420 --> 00:24:50.220
- How old are you?
- Thirteen.

185
00:24:51.830 --> 00:24:53.840
- And you know me?
- Yes.

186
00:24:54.540 --> 00:24:56.870
- What do you know about me?
- I know your house.

187
00:24:59.190 --> 00:25:01.480
- You know my name?
- Don Alejandro.

188
00:25:02.970 --> 00:25:05.990
- How long have you known me?
- For many years.

189
00:25:07.200 --> 00:25:08.380
For many years.

190
00:25:08.990 --> 00:25:11.590
Well... we arrived.

191
00:25:12.730 --> 00:25:14.020
Your father is a policeman?

192
00:25:18.140 --> 00:25:18.900
Your penknife.

193
00:25:20.910 --> 00:25:22.740
Can I keep a pencil and feathers?

194
00:25:24.910 --> 00:25:26.870
- Will we meet again?
- Maybe.

195
00:25:28.700 --> 00:25:30.780
- Bye.
- Bye.

196
00:25:38.420 --> 00:25:39.590
I knew your wife.

197
00:26:09.890 --> 00:26:14.220
Do you have to be so noisy. doll?
What do you think it is. stables?

198
00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:17.530
You and I will talk about it later.

199
00:26:20.070 --> 00:26:21.750
Ale. home.

200
00:26:28.500 --> 00:26:30.360
- Has anyone called?
- No.

201
00:26:31.250 --> 00:26:32.660
- What about yesterday?
- No.

202
00:26:34.240 --> 00:26:36.600
- And no one has come. no?
- Nobody ever comes here.

203
00:26:37.860 --> 00:26:38.780
Anything else?

204
00:27:02.610 --> 00:27:04.030
Police station.

205
00:27:06.310 --> 00:27:07.790
Police station. hello.

206
00:27:10.480 --> 00:27:11.350
Hello?

207
00:27:23.520 --> 00:27:25.060
- What were you doing today?
- Nothing.

208
00:27:25.610 --> 00:27:28.530
Nothing? I found out that you
was climbing trees again.

209
00:27:28.610 --> 00:27:32.270
- Me?
- You. A naughty tomboy.

210
00:27:32.830 --> 00:27:36.330
And I know who is to blame.
Much mime and very little authority.

211
00:27:37.260 --> 00:27:40.130
- What does that suppose to mean?
- I'm the only one who cares.

212
00:27:42.070 --> 00:27:44.640
- Bon Appetit.
- Thank you.

213
00:27:44.920 --> 00:27:46.270
Rest. rest.

214
00:27:51.430 --> 00:27:53.470
- Will you join us?
- I just had dinner.

215
00:27:56.040 --> 00:27:56.900
And you?

216
00:27:57.380 --> 00:27:59.500
- Have you climbed up the roof?
- That's a lie.

217
00:27:59.790 --> 00:28:01.450
- I never lie.
- Me neither.

218
00:28:01.730 --> 00:28:04.010
Enough Gregoria. And you eat.

219
00:28:04.800 --> 00:28:07.490
The door to the attic is opened.
like last year.

220
00:28:07.590 --> 00:28:09.440
- It's not me.
- Who was it then?

221
00:28:10.430 --> 00:28:12.350
And the window is broken.
who did it?

222
00:28:13.250 --> 00:28:17.650
It's her. who else can it be?
I told you to eat.

223
00:28:18.170 --> 00:28:22.760
And you. what a view. Manolin?
Go to bed now.

224
00:28:22.761 --> 00:28:23.761
On Sunday you will stay at home.

225
00:28:23.800 --> 00:28:25.330
- Why?
- Because I said so!

226
00:28:34.530 --> 00:28:37.830
- Say goodnight to the Sergeant.
- Good evening. Sergeant.

227
00:28:38.380 --> 00:28:40.350
Good night. Goyita.

228
00:29:05.240 --> 00:29:06.650
Are you hungry. Goyita?

229
00:29:09.850 --> 00:29:10.890
Do not worry.

230
00:29:12.430 --> 00:29:14.860
I will look after you and
I'll teach you to fly.

231
00:29:29.840 --> 00:29:30.710
Don Alejandro!

232
00:29:36.670 --> 00:29:37.580
Are you talking to me?

233
00:29:39.090 --> 00:29:40.760
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

234
00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.660
- How do you know my name?
- I've been here three years.

235
00:29:45.100 --> 00:29:47.910
- You do not know mine. Marisa Marcos.
- Pleased to meet you.

236
00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:52.430
I wanted to apologize for what happened
the other day.

237
00:29:52.431 --> 00:29:53.431
I threw you from the theater
without the slightest consideration.

238
00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:57.590
- Why are you laughing?

239
00:29:57.591 --> 00:29:59.591
- Because we've seen each other twice
and we've apologized at least six times.

240
00:30:01.660 --> 00:30:05.660
The fault was mine. I confess
I was surprised to see Macbeth.

241
00:30:06.040 --> 00:30:09.760
- Not a play for children.
- Yeah. but they chose it.

242
00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:13.450
I must admit I had some doubts
at the beginning.

243
00:30:13.940 --> 00:30:16.630
They should have done the
"The Girl with the Jug" as every year.

244
00:30:17.520 --> 00:30:21.040
It's a lie. I do not regret anything.
They'll be just fine.

245
00:30:23.510 --> 00:30:28.030
- I hope you will come at the opening.
- Well... I don't promise anything.

246
00:30:29.210 --> 00:30:32.820
I'm unpredictable.
And Lady Macbeth?

247
00:30:35.240 --> 00:30:36.390
She's very interesting.

248
00:30:38.100 --> 00:30:41.060
- Is she punished?
- No. She decided to study acting.

249
00:30:41.940 --> 00:30:43.930
- Voluntarily.
- I see.

250
00:30:45.170 --> 00:30:48.400
Children today are very different
from us as we were.

251
00:30:49.730 --> 00:30:52.380
I speak for my generation.
not yours. of course.

252
00:30:53.910 --> 00:30:57.540
Was pleased to meet you. I wish
I had a teacher like you.

253
00:31:48.870 --> 00:31:52.210
- Good afternoon. senorita.
- Good afternoon. signor.

254
00:31:54.170 --> 00:31:59.040
I am looking for something...
very. very special.

255
00:32:01.450 --> 00:32:04.001
A pair of Katiuska boots size 43.

256
00:32:04.312 --> 00:32:06.753
I'm sorry. we have those only in 17.

257
00:32:08.137 --> 00:32:11.884
Well. then give me size 16.

258
00:32:13.580 --> 00:32:14.880
They always were 17.

259
00:32:20.290 --> 00:32:22.040
You sure are 17.

260
00:32:22.830 --> 00:32:26.080
- You're crazy. and if a customer enters.
what will happen to my reputation?

261
00:32:26.081 --> 00:32:28.081
- I don't give a damn about
the customers or your reputation.

262
00:32:28.310 --> 00:32:29.390
But not here.

263
00:32:31.760 --> 00:32:34.320
I tell you I don't give a damn about
the customers or your reputation.

264
00:32:37.010 --> 00:32:39.190
- You seem different.
- Me?

265
00:32:40.100 --> 00:32:43.960
- You have come a month earlier.

266
00:32:43.961 --> 00:32:45.961
- This is not an official visit.
I needed to see you today.

267
00:32:48.120 --> 00:32:52.030
You know. you asked me yourself
to come more often.

268
00:32:58.290 --> 00:32:59.650
- Hello.

269
00:32:59.651 --> 00:33:01.651
- Hello. We have come
to remind you about tonight.

270
00:33:02.410 --> 00:33:06.850
The film society. the end of the season.
Will you come?

271
00:33:09.030 --> 00:33:12.840
Alejandro... Alvaro... Amaya.

272
00:33:13.820 --> 00:33:16.810
Alejandro is my lover.
He came this morning. day of sex.

273
00:33:18.110 --> 00:33:19.070
Shall we go?

274
00:33:19.900 --> 00:33:21.750
- Whatever you say.

275
00:33:21.751 --> 00:33:22.751
- Don't you afraid of
the young people. Alejandro?

276
00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:26.860
- Make sure you come. okay?
It's twenty pesetas.

277
00:33:26.861 --> 00:33:27.861
- Bye. Chao.

278
00:33:33.150 --> 00:33:37.840
You're a witch. You've mocked me.
You can't be old. huh?

279
00:33:38.270 --> 00:33:45.630
The old. to the grave. And you ashamed
to be seen with me. So you laugh at me.

280
00:33:46.210 --> 00:33:48.560
You don't understand anything.
Let's go.

281
00:33:53.310 --> 00:33:54.400
What are you doing?

282
00:34:01.450 --> 00:34:03.930
What's wrong.
something happened?

283
00:34:04.810 --> 00:34:05.930
You can't hide it from me.

284
00:34:28.970 --> 00:34:30.910
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

285
00:34:31.510 --> 00:34:33.780
- Can I see Don Alejandro?
- What do you want?

286
00:34:42.140 --> 00:34:43.880
Wait. I'm coming!

287
00:34:52.140 --> 00:34:52.980
Hello. little one.

288
00:34:55.620 --> 00:34:56.510
What a surprise.

289
00:34:59.020 --> 00:35:00.070
You came alone?

290
00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:06.570
Wouldn't your parents get mad?
Good girls should not leave home alone.

291
00:35:06.571 --> 00:35:07.571
especially without a permit.

292
00:35:12.800 --> 00:35:13.610
Would you like to have dinner?

293
00:35:15.310 --> 00:35:17.380
- Do you want a Cura�ao.
as they say on TV?

294
00:35:17.381 --> 00:35:18.381
- Goodbye.

295
00:35:21.880 --> 00:35:25.540
Where were you? I didn't know
anything about you.

296
00:35:26.100 --> 00:35:28.030
- I've looked everywhere.
- I was here yesterday.

297
00:35:30.670 --> 00:35:34.070
- Where were you?
- In Madrid.

298
00:35:35.420 --> 00:35:38.450
- Business.
- I don't want you to come to school.

299
00:35:39.950 --> 00:35:41.610
And you shouldn't speak
with Miss Marisa.

300
00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.280
Never again. I promise.

301
00:35:48.160 --> 00:35:50.140
- Why do you have a beard?
It makes you old.

302
00:35:50.141 --> 00:35:52.141
- You want me to get rid of it?

303
00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:53.600
No.

304
00:35:56.380 --> 00:36:00.050
- Is it the goldfinch?
- No. the coal tit.

305
00:36:03.180 --> 00:36:08.000
- What is this?
- Talisman. A memory about the camp.

306
00:36:08.610 --> 00:36:09.880
- What camp?

307
00:36:09.881 --> 00:36:11.881
- Concentration camp.
where Francoists put me.

308
00:36:14.700 --> 00:36:17.710
- How did you know my wife?
- She was collecting nests.

309
00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:23.550
- The coal tit.
- No. the goldfinch.

310
00:36:23.620 --> 00:36:25.490
As I said. the goldfinch.

311
00:38:30.790 --> 00:38:31.750
What are you singing?

312
00:38:36.270 --> 00:38:37.950
Manuel will be angry.

313
00:38:38.630 --> 00:38:40.400
- Why?
- Because of the bird.

314
00:38:40.670 --> 00:38:44.070
- I do with it what I want.
- Mama says that you must respect him.

315
00:38:47.850 --> 00:38:52.260
Hey... are you going to marry
a civil guard?

316
00:38:52.430 --> 00:38:54.550
- No way.
- Me neither.

317
00:38:56.300 --> 00:38:58.940
Goyita has a boyfriend.
Goyita has a boyfriend!

318
00:38:59.030 --> 00:39:00.670
- It's a lie!
- It's true. everybody knows it.

319
00:39:00.671 --> 00:39:02.671
I'll die right now if it's a lie.

320
00:39:02.780 --> 00:39:05.470
- He is not a boyfriend.
- He is a holy fool.

321
00:39:08.620 --> 00:39:11.330
- And what is that?
- I don't know.

322
00:39:12.990 --> 00:39:15.900
- What does it mean?
- No idea.

323
00:39:17.270 --> 00:39:20.210
Sgt Manuel called him called so.

324
00:39:20.870 --> 00:39:23.200
The sergeant is a jerk.
and you too.

325
00:39:23.310 --> 00:39:25.900
- And you a thousand times worse.
- And you're a million times worse.

326
00:39:26.140 --> 00:39:28.180
- And you infinitely worse.
- You're an idiot.

327
00:39:28.360 --> 00:39:31.760
- A holy fool. a holy fool!
- A friend. a friend!

328
00:39:32.340 --> 00:39:35.400
You want me to come
and put you in bed?!

329
00:39:35.590 --> 00:39:39.040
- A holy fool. a holy fool...
- A friend!

330
00:39:46.210 --> 00:39:48.400
I do not care if everybody knows.

331
00:39:50.230 --> 00:39:51.970
And if Manuel finds out. so be it.

332
00:39:55.820 --> 00:39:59.120
I do not know what to do.

333
00:40:02.550 --> 00:40:04.010
I am a normal man.

334
00:40:06.250 --> 00:40:10.710
- However. I only think about that...
young girl.

335
00:40:10.711 --> 00:40:11.711
- Not so young.

336
00:40:12.860 --> 00:40:14.970
If I didn't know you. I would have
complained to the authorities.

337
00:40:15.110 --> 00:40:17.000
- Oh. I'm serious.
- Me too.

338
00:40:31.020 --> 00:40:34.160
- You invited me and don't even
have a wine to spare. Miser.

339
00:40:34.161 --> 00:40:36.160
I won't come here any more.
- Damn priests.

340
00:40:37.180 --> 00:40:40.500
Always asking and asking.

341
00:40:41.410 --> 00:40:46.510
- You are like cockroaches.
- Oh. how he barks.

342
00:40:50.360 --> 00:40:52.500
And what will happen
when her father hear about you?

343
00:40:53.690 --> 00:40:57.250
- Do you know he is a civil guard?
- I haven't done anything wrong.

344
00:41:00.140 --> 00:41:00.940
Even here.

345
00:41:03.480 --> 00:41:06.490
- I've known a saying...
- No. deprive me of it. Eladio.

346
00:41:09.030 --> 00:41:10.200
No fooling. Alejandro.

347
00:41:25.520 --> 00:41:26.720
You're all alone. right?

348
00:41:29.670 --> 00:41:30.530
And you?

349
00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:35.200
- I have the Lord up there.
- You sure are smart.

350
00:41:40.530 --> 00:41:41.490
Why don't you marry?

351
00:41:43.390 --> 00:41:44.210
With whom?

352
00:41:44.860 --> 00:41:48.550
- With the girl from Salamanca. satyr.
- Who told you about her?

353
00:41:49.500 --> 00:41:51.800
- You.
- I talk too much.

354
00:41:58.300 --> 00:42:00.480
Damn. you live swell.

355
00:42:07.230 --> 00:42:08.280
And I live swell.

356
00:42:12.040 --> 00:42:13.800
If I give you the chance.
the holy leader.

357
00:42:15.410 --> 00:42:18.570
- The lord knows that
their pastors are human.

358
00:42:18.571 --> 00:42:19.571
- Ya. ya. of course.

359
00:42:31.120 --> 00:42:32.820
Why not send habits to hell?

360
00:42:35.910 --> 00:42:38.370
Have you ever felt like sleeping
with a woman. no?

361
00:42:39.620 --> 00:42:43.880
It would not be the first time.
When I became a priest and...

362
00:42:44.580 --> 00:42:47.970
- And then...
- Why not to try. right?

363
00:42:49.610 --> 00:42:51.690
You seal her and you bless her.

364
00:43:05.400 --> 00:43:07.160
Father. what happened to me?

365
00:43:16.610 --> 00:43:20.460
Son... you're old.

366
00:43:27.180 --> 00:43:31.190
- Do you know how old she is?
- 110 years.

367
00:43:39.220 --> 00:43:40.650
Can you imagine what she said
the other day?

368
00:43:42.350 --> 00:43:44.400
She asked me where I had been.

369
00:43:46.370 --> 00:43:49.200
And I lied.
without any hesitation.

370
00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:54.400
In 12 years of marriage I had never
lied to poor Isabel. never.

371
00:43:57.530 --> 00:44:02.720
- The girl is a witch...
- It's horrible.

372
00:44:04.290 --> 00:44:09.280
I do not know if I'm turning
into a monster or a fool.

373
00:44:11.450 --> 00:44:13.380
In both. Alejandro.

374
00:44:16.610 --> 00:44:17.360
What would you do in my place?

375
00:44:18.850 --> 00:44:20.340
- Don't insult me.
- No. really.

376
00:44:22.850 --> 00:44:27.150
You're still a moron.

377
00:44:28.170 --> 00:44:29.460
Never monster.

378
00:44:32.690 --> 00:44:35.070
Some day I will do as you say.
father.

379
00:44:37.410 --> 00:44:41.390
- All this is yours?
- Yes.

380
00:44:43.380 --> 00:44:45.820
- You never come to Mass?
- No.

381
00:44:46.540 --> 00:44:51.280
- But you are a friend of the priest?
- What can I say?

382
00:44:52.110 --> 00:44:53.410
What is holy fool?

383
00:44:57.090 --> 00:45:01.060
Well... it is a guy who
stands out of his environment.

384
00:45:02.980 --> 00:45:10.970
He is doing things which others don't.
Solitary. obsessed with music. chess.

385
00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:13.830
with the shotguns.

386
00:45:16.290 --> 00:45:24.470
He has a beard. and sometimes.
sometimes. he wears a denim hat.

387
00:45:28.370 --> 00:45:30.400
The sergeant says
you're a holy fool.

388
00:45:32.970 --> 00:45:35.950
- He'll know. Are you staying for dinner?
- Okay.

389
00:45:37.270 --> 00:45:40.200
Cesar. tell to Amparo
to call the police.

390
00:45:41.040 --> 00:45:47.750
And say. to whom is on duty. that Goya
Menendez is eating with her school friend.

391
00:45:51.600 --> 00:45:52.570
You heard it.

392
00:45:57.360 --> 00:45:59.700
Goyita. it is not right
to lie to your parents.

393
00:46:02.010 --> 00:46:05.590
Goyita. listen. it is not right
to lie to your parents.

394
00:46:05.591 --> 00:46:07.591
or anyone else.
especially when there is no reason.

395
00:46:12.090 --> 00:46:15.450
- Don't you ever lie?
- Almost never.

396
00:46:17.330 --> 00:46:20.810
- And your wife. do you ever lied to her?
- No.

397
00:46:25.150 --> 00:46:26.970
How do you know
if there is a reason or not?

398
00:46:30.160 --> 00:46:32.680
- Because I am an old man.
and you. a young girl.

399
00:46:32.681 --> 00:46:34.681
- What?

400
00:46:37.970 --> 00:46:43.200
- Because I am an adult and you're a child.
and your parents...

401
00:46:43.201 --> 00:46:44.201
- Goodbye.

402
00:46:48.870 --> 00:46:55.160
There is reason. of course there reason.
You were right to say that.

403
00:46:55.161 --> 00:46:57.161
We must be cautious.

404
00:47:00.190 --> 00:47:01.520
Don't go. please.

405
00:47:04.620 --> 00:47:06.980
The sergeant told my father
not to let me come here.

406
00:47:10.560 --> 00:47:15.040
- Sorry. I do not like the Civil Guard.
- Great.

407
00:47:18.120 --> 00:47:22.960
- Want to ride?
- No. Show me the room where she slept.

408
00:47:51.080 --> 00:47:54.000
- Here she slept?
- Yes.

409
00:47:54.890 --> 00:47:56.480
- And you?
- Also.

410
00:47:57.700 --> 00:47:58.980
- Well. let's go.
- Wait.

411
00:48:01.650 --> 00:48:04.560
- This was hers?
- Yes.

412
00:48:06.480 --> 00:48:09.270
- She wasn't like me.
- She was very pretty.

413
00:48:10.780 --> 00:48:11.910
Short and stout.

414
00:48:13.510 --> 00:48:15.600
- What?
- Not much breast.

415
00:48:17.740 --> 00:48:18.790
Let's leave that.

416
00:48:31.710 --> 00:48:37.900
- Now where you sleep?
- Somewhere else. Come on. Goyita.

417
00:48:57.120 --> 00:48:59.420
I heard that you married for money.

418
00:49:01.990 --> 00:49:05.230
- That you were starving.
- That's a lie!

419
00:49:05.480 --> 00:49:09.470
I never would have married for money.
not with her or anyone! You hear that?!

420
00:49:12.460 --> 00:49:14.610
- She died in this bed?
- And you. what do you care?

421
00:49:14.660 --> 00:49:16.020
- Wait.
- Wait what?!

422
00:49:16.650 --> 00:49:20.530
I don't think you married for money.
or that you were dying of hunger.

423
00:49:24.230 --> 00:49:26.690
- Thank you.
- You don't have any children. right?

424
00:49:28.550 --> 00:49:31.530
- No.
- Is it her fault or yours?

425
00:49:32.790 --> 00:49:34.210
Because of her. of course.

426
00:49:41.090 --> 00:49:42.460
What was the last thing
she told you?

427
00:49:44.610 --> 00:49:47.500
Beware of girls
who ask too many questions.

428
00:49:50.060 --> 00:49:54.440
- Did she suffer much?
- Not as much as me.

429
00:50:16.210 --> 00:50:19.060
- What's this?
- Vicisuas.

430
00:50:19.910 --> 00:50:22.380
- What?!
- Vi-si-suas.

431
00:50:22.990 --> 00:50:26.130
- Is it a kind of gazpacho?
- More or less.

432
00:50:30.630 --> 00:50:33.030
- Where are you from?
- De Alcoy. and you?

433
00:50:33.500 --> 00:50:34.810
From Ciudad Rodrigo.

434
00:50:36.800 --> 00:50:39.070
- Your whole family was in the Civil Guard?
- No. my grandfather was a pastor.

435
00:50:39.071 --> 00:50:41.071
What about yours?

436
00:50:41.600 --> 00:50:43.250
My grandfather was also a pastor.

437
00:50:46.070 --> 00:50:47.870
At home they let me take
a little of wine.

438
00:50:48.080 --> 00:50:49.850
- White or red?
- Red.

439
00:50:51.520 --> 00:50:54.650
Red. the girl drinks red wine.

440
00:51:01.870 --> 00:51:03.740
For a long and beautiful friendship.

441
00:51:11.890 --> 00:51:16.190
Goyita... nothing.

442
00:51:23.460 --> 00:51:28.330
- You have such dinner every day?
- No. not at all.

443
00:51:28.331 --> 00:51:30.331
Today is a special meal.
just for you.

444
00:51:37.870 --> 00:51:40.070
- On the right.
- What?

445
00:51:40.350 --> 00:51:42.250
- The knife.
- What knife?

446
00:51:47.620 --> 00:51:48.510
Okay.

447
00:51:54.630 --> 00:51:58.740
- Why are you laughing?
- It was long ago...

448
00:51:58.741 --> 00:52:00.741
...since I taught another person
to eat fish.

449
00:52:02.860 --> 00:52:05.460
- I know whom.
- And she wasn't stout.

450
00:52:06.580 --> 00:52:07.440
Right.

451
00:52:22.060 --> 00:52:22.870
Are these the ones?

452
00:52:26.960 --> 00:52:28.940
Because of them
you were angry at her?

453
00:52:32.220 --> 00:52:34.490
But you didn't write
any notes to her?

454
00:52:37.130 --> 00:52:40.280
What about me? Why me?

455
00:52:45.050 --> 00:52:48.050
You know that I don't collect nests.

456
00:52:52.220 --> 00:52:54.280
- Why?
- For everything.

457
00:52:56.800 --> 00:52:57.560
For everything?

458
00:53:00.270 --> 00:53:01.060
Me too.

459
00:53:08.660 --> 00:53:11.050
The nests are horrible
out of trees.

460
00:53:13.030 --> 00:53:14.580
It is an opinion like any other.

461
00:53:24.410 --> 00:53:26.300
Do you want me to tell Cesar
to take you home?

462
00:53:26.350 --> 00:53:28.310
- No. I want you to take me.
- Me?

463
00:53:29.260 --> 00:53:31.270
- I thought you had said that
we should be cautious.

464
00:53:31.271 --> 00:53:32.271
- That's what you said.

465
00:53:37.880 --> 00:53:39.330
Get in. my Lady.

466
00:54:15.800 --> 00:54:20.710
It was a beautiful Sunday. It was a long
ago since I had such a good time.

467
00:54:22.570 --> 00:54:23.280
Do you like me?

468
00:54:27.640 --> 00:54:30.770
You are a child...

469
00:54:32.360 --> 00:54:35.310
...very sensitive and very smart.

470
00:54:35.660 --> 00:54:38.210
No. I mean as a woman.

471
00:54:41.050 --> 00:54:44.330
As a woman?
What a thing to say.

472
00:54:47.150 --> 00:54:50.040
- I never know when you're
serious or joking.

473
00:54:50.041 --> 00:54:52.041
- If you don't like me. I don't
want to see you.

474
00:54:53.280 --> 00:54:54.690
Never again will I see you.

475
00:54:58.340 --> 00:55:04.200
I like you. Goya. of course I like you.
I like you as a woman.

476
00:55:05.600 --> 00:55:12.150
I can't stop thinking of you.
That's not normal. Goya. It's terrible.

477
00:55:14.240 --> 00:55:15.040
You may kiss me.

478
00:55:24.700 --> 00:55:27.850
If they tell you something bad about me.
do not believe them.

479
00:55:29.120 --> 00:55:30.000
I won't.

480
00:55:33.150 --> 00:55:35.830
- For everything.
- For everything.

481
00:55:37.450 --> 00:55:40.150
- Forever.
- Forever.

482
00:55:44.450 --> 00:55:46.690
On Tuesday after school.
I would go to the forest.

483
00:55:46.691 --> 00:55:48.691
to see if there are any new nests.

484
00:55:55.360 --> 00:55:58.840
- You need the whole opera?
- Well. only the key moments.

485
00:55:59.510 --> 00:56:02.900
There is a Verdi opera
with the theme of Macbeth.

486
00:56:05.010 --> 00:56:07.990
But if you let me say so.
I hate him.

487
00:56:08.660 --> 00:56:11.860
- No problem.
- There is also Strauss. Grieg. Smetana.

488
00:56:11.861 --> 00:56:12.861
When will it be?

489
00:56:13.340 --> 00:56:15.930
- End of the act.
- I would suggest Smetana.

490
00:56:16.330 --> 00:56:18.930
I can take care of the sound.
if you want.

491
00:56:19.880 --> 00:56:22.500
- I don't want to bother you so much.
- You don't.

492
00:56:24.550 --> 00:56:29.260
- Why did you choose...
what was her name. Lady Macbeth?

493
00:56:29.261 --> 00:56:30.261
- Gregoria Menendez.

494
00:56:33.120 --> 00:56:35.510
Because she is evil enough
to understand the role.

495
00:56:38.600 --> 00:56:39.580
And you?

496
00:56:42.310 --> 00:56:44.770
Why did you choose Goyita?
Goyita is almost a woman.

497
00:56:46.010 --> 00:56:48.270
- What do you mean by that?
- Nothing.

498
00:56:52.050 --> 00:56:53.130
- Please. have a sit?
- Thank you.

499
00:56:53.740 --> 00:56:55.430
No. no. not here.

500
00:56:58.740 --> 00:57:01.500
- You have a beautiful house.
- Nothing special.

501
00:57:02.820 --> 00:57:07.920
- Her love for birds. I mean Goyita's.
is it your influence?

502
00:57:07.921 --> 00:57:08.921
- No.

503
00:57:09.230 --> 00:57:12.210
- I like dogs.
- With milk or with lemon?

504
00:57:12.650 --> 00:57:13.980
- The dogs?
- The tea.

505
00:57:14.390 --> 00:57:15.530
With lemon.

506
00:57:29.740 --> 00:57:35.120
It's funny... I always thought that
women are much smarter than men.

507
00:57:36.780 --> 00:57:38.130
And much more evil.

508
00:57:43.930 --> 00:57:45.510
The music was an excuse. right?

509
00:57:48.400 --> 00:57:51.760
- You do not have to worry about me.
I'm quite harmless.

510
00:57:51.761 --> 00:57:53.761
- Not really.

511
00:57:55.250 --> 00:57:58.400
This is the best thing I have said
to myself for the last thousand years.

512
00:58:02.240 --> 00:58:04.500
Do you know that Goyita
forbade me to talk to you?

513
00:58:07.060 --> 00:58:09.400
In all the jokes is always
a seed of truth. right?

514
00:58:13.580 --> 00:58:17.850
Here! Alejandro!

515
00:58:20.460 --> 00:58:24.350
- Goya!
- Alejandro. where are you?

516
00:58:25.780 --> 00:58:30.620
Stop these games. Goyita!
Where are you?

517
00:58:33.460 --> 00:58:34.960
Alejandro!

518
00:58:38.440 --> 00:58:39.300
Goya!

519
00:58:45.180 --> 00:58:46.280
Goyita!

520
00:58:50.880 --> 00:58:53.430
- You want to make me angry. eh.
- Hello.

521
00:59:04.720 --> 00:59:06.080
It's not funny.

522
00:59:06.450 --> 00:59:10.690
- I just found a nest of warbler.

523
00:59:10.691 --> 00:59:12.691
- I don't care about the warbler. but
one of these days you'll fall down.

524
00:59:13.740 --> 00:59:17.460
- And you will kill yourself.
- So that I will die before you.

525
00:59:19.190 --> 00:59:20.870
And you will take me
to the cemetery.

526
00:59:22.010 --> 00:59:26.020
And you'll bury me next to her.
Bit you won't. eh? No.

527
00:59:28.180 --> 00:59:32.810
You are old and dirty. but
I don't want to be away from you.

528
00:59:32.811 --> 00:59:33.811
We'll never separate.

529
00:59:35.140 --> 00:59:38.230
When you're older and dirtier.
I'll take care of you.

530
00:59:38.231 --> 00:59:40.231
and after you die
I'll look after your house.

531
00:59:41.650 --> 00:59:42.780
But we need to get married.

532
00:59:44.750 --> 00:59:47.130
Ah. right there. at St. Thomas.

533
00:59:47.500 --> 00:59:49.540
- No need for a priest or a paper.
- No?

534
00:59:49.920 --> 00:59:56.560
No. We put our hands and blood together.
so we can't separate anymore.

535
00:59:56.561 --> 00:59:57.561
forever and ever.

536
00:59:57.640 --> 00:59:58.530
What blood?

537
00:59:59.540 --> 01:00:04.360
With this knife. I will cut "G"
in your hand. and you "A" in mine.

538
01:00:05.170 --> 01:00:07.410
- And we join our blood.
- Are you crazy?

539
01:00:08.670 --> 01:00:10.940
- Are you afraid?
- No. it's for you.

540
01:00:10.941 --> 01:00:11.941
Where will you go
with the severed hand?

541
01:00:12.580 --> 01:00:13.450
Well.

542
01:00:15.540 --> 01:00:17.560
Goya. don't run
with the knife in your hand!

543
01:00:19.300 --> 01:00:25.200
Goya. Goyita. pardon me.
I didn't want to offend you.

544
01:00:30.430 --> 01:00:32.790
I told you not to see
Senorita Marisa again.

545
01:00:34.100 --> 01:00:35.650
- Why not?
- Because I said so.

546
01:00:38.530 --> 01:00:42.290
She came to ask me for the music
for the play. I didn't call her.

547
01:00:43.540 --> 01:00:45.140
You understand that
if she comes to my place...

548
01:00:48.420 --> 01:00:52.970
Well. why should I apologize to
a young girl! And don't bite your nails!

549
01:00:53.590 --> 01:00:59.460
I don't take orders from anyone. and I take
to my house whoever I want! Damn you!

550
01:01:14.820 --> 01:01:16.180
- Can I come in?
- Come.

551
01:01:29.020 --> 01:01:35.590
It will have blood. they say!
Stones have been known to move.

552
01:01:37.650 --> 01:01:43.500
- ... what is the night?
- Almost at odds with morning.

553
01:01:46.340 --> 01:01:48.800
No. Goya. I will not hurt you.

554
01:01:50.130 --> 01:01:52.850
- What if someone see us?
- Is that what you care?

555
01:02:14.140 --> 01:02:19.980
We will always be together. forever
and ever. And never shall we part.

556
01:02:21.990 --> 01:02:26.670
Because we joined our blood.
in this secret pact.

557
01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:35.520
Now you have to give me something.

558
01:02:46.820 --> 01:02:49.190
Don't show it to anyone.

559
01:02:57.120 --> 01:03:01.210
- And the last thing...
- What?

560
01:03:02.830 --> 01:03:05.680
You must burn all her pictures
and all her clothes.

561
01:03:08.820 --> 01:03:12.420
No. Goya. I can't.

562
01:03:17.510 --> 01:03:19.980
- No way.
- Well.

563
01:03:23.410 --> 01:03:24.790
I don't want you to come with me.

564
01:03:31.340 --> 01:03:36.010
The cryptogams or plants without flowers
are divided into... Thallophytes.

565
01:03:37.100 --> 01:03:40.380
Bryophytes and Pteridophytas.

566
01:03:41.290 --> 01:03:45.600
- Plants that lack chlorophyll must take it
from the others. They are called parasites...

567
01:03:45.601 --> 01:03:46.601
- Wait.

568
01:03:48.390 --> 01:03:49.310
Show me your hand.

569
01:03:54.780 --> 01:03:55.650
Both.

570
01:03:56.630 --> 01:03:57.520
Children!

571
01:04:03.320 --> 01:04:07.130
Don't be a clown. Goya.
Who did this?

572
01:04:07.580 --> 01:04:10.590
- Nobody.
- What does it mean?

573
01:04:11.050 --> 01:04:14.040
- Nothing.
- Well. I see a large 'A'.

574
01:04:15.090 --> 01:04:17.080
- Or not so large?
- Yes!

575
01:04:22.310 --> 01:04:25.170
Very funny. Let's see.

576
01:04:25.410 --> 01:04:30.040
Antonio. Alberto. Adelino and Agust�n.
Alberto?

577
01:04:32.830 --> 01:04:35.150
Adelino? It is "P".

578
01:04:35.840 --> 01:04:38.200
No need to get up.

579
01:04:38.900 --> 01:04:40.760
Agust�n? It is "N".

580
01:04:42.430 --> 01:04:46.890
Margarita. Valdes and... at your service.

581
01:04:48.500 --> 01:04:49.290
Sit.

582
01:04:50.580 --> 01:04:54.510
Now. hands up all those
with an initial.

583
01:04:54.810 --> 01:04:59.670
- Me! Me! Me!
- That also goes with you. Gregoria.

584
01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:07.930
You're all savages. To me
this love is all right.

585
01:05:08.740 --> 01:05:12.280
among children it is precious.
and quite normal.

586
01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:17.810
but what is not normal is that it is done
with blood. and you could get infection.

587
01:05:18.170 --> 01:05:22.640
And taking this opportunity.
tomorrow we will study hands.

588
01:05:22.641 --> 01:05:24.641
including nails. necks and ears.

589
01:05:26.170 --> 01:05:29.360
- Goyita. you was very good.
Want to help me at the theater?

590
01:05:29.361 --> 01:05:30.361
- Okay.

591
01:05:30.880 --> 01:05:31.790
Sit down.

592
01:05:35.010 --> 01:05:37.130
Pilar Campos. lesson 17.

593
01:05:37.510 --> 01:05:42.284
There are some animals that parasites
on others. There are also plants...

594
01:05:42.955 --> 01:05:47.367
that are parasitic. like mistletoe.
fungi and others.

595
01:05:50.850 --> 01:05:52.410
- Can I come in?
- Who is it?

596
01:05:52.730 --> 01:05:54.640
- Goyita.
- Come in. Goyita.

597
01:05:55.920 --> 01:05:56.860
Are you free?

598
01:05:59.440 --> 01:06:03.950
Like it?
Then climb here and help me.

599
01:06:08.510 --> 01:06:10.670
- Can you mix colors?
- Yes.

600
01:06:11.340 --> 01:06:12.910
Look. it's that over there.

601
01:06:13.640 --> 01:06:15.260
- This one?
- Yes.

602
01:06:16.800 --> 01:06:18.730
- And how?

603
01:06:18.731 --> 01:06:21.731
- Ultramarine with ground of Seville.
English red and white.

604
01:06:24.010 --> 01:06:28.580
There are the buckets.
Use that robe.

605
01:06:36.400 --> 01:06:40.670
Let's make a deal? I ask you
one thing I want you to answer.

606
01:06:41.570 --> 01:06:45.830
and you ask me something you want
to know about me. But on two conditions:

607
01:06:47.030 --> 01:06:52.490
We must tell the truth.
and we mustn't tell anyone. okay?

608
01:06:55.390 --> 01:06:58.890
- And what do you want to know?
- You begin.

609
01:06:59.610 --> 01:07:00.750
How old are you?

610
01:07:05.620 --> 01:07:06.560
24.

611
01:07:07.440 --> 01:07:12.190
- Who is your favorite pupil?
- Sorry. now my turn.

612
01:07:13.410 --> 01:07:14.500
Use these gloves.

613
01:07:17.270 --> 01:07:19.090
- Do you like it at school?
- No.

614
01:07:19.690 --> 01:07:23.690
- Why?
- Sorry. now my turn.

615
01:07:26.420 --> 01:07:27.470
Is Lore your favorite?

616
01:07:29.310 --> 01:07:33.290
Not exactly favorite. Goyita.
and you know it yourself.

617
01:07:34.280 --> 01:07:36.200
Whom I most like is Pilar Campos.

618
01:07:37.730 --> 01:07:41.560
- It is a very particular affection. Goya.
- Pilar Campos?

619
01:07:42.240 --> 01:07:48.050
- It's a stupid subject. Let's hear
why don't you like school?

620
01:07:48.051 --> 01:07:50.051
- I don't like to be locked up.

621
01:07:50.700 --> 01:07:51.560
Oh.

622
01:07:54.500 --> 01:08:00.520
- You don't like me?
- No. no. on the contrary.

623
01:08:01.250 --> 01:08:04.130
I love you. Goya. and there is
no question about that.

624
01:08:10.410 --> 01:08:13.010
- What does 'A' mean?
- You already know.

625
01:08:13.260 --> 01:08:15.640
- You say it.
- Alejandro.

626
01:08:19.680 --> 01:08:25.090
- What is going to be in tomorrow's test?
- Goya. you can't ask such question.

627
01:08:25.540 --> 01:08:29.050
- If you don't want. stop playing.
- You should be ashamed of yourself.

628
01:08:33.890 --> 01:08:38.860
First. how clouds form.
Second. what is the psychometric.

629
01:08:39.700 --> 01:08:44.230
Third. anticyclones and depressions.
And fourth. the air in the temperate zone.

630
01:08:44.840 --> 01:08:48.200
- And don't change anything.
- I never cheat.

631
01:08:53.640 --> 01:08:56.500
- He has 'G'?
- Yes.

632
01:09:00.690 --> 01:09:01.820
Why did you go to see him?

633
01:09:05.390 --> 01:09:07.340
Because I wanted to know
if he was a trustworthy person.

634
01:09:08.180 --> 01:09:10.740
- And does he?
- It's my turn.

635
01:09:21.180 --> 01:09:22.630
What do you do
when you are together?

636
01:09:25.650 --> 01:09:32.080
We talk. play... he tells me things.

637
01:09:33.570 --> 01:09:40.530
listen to music. cycling. shooting.

638
01:09:42.550 --> 01:09:44.800
Nothing more. I promise.

639
01:09:47.540 --> 01:09:50.720
Too much ground of Seville and
you lack ultramarine.

640
01:09:58.330 --> 01:10:00.660
- Do you have a boyfriend?

641
01:10:00.661 --> 01:10:02.661
- Well. it depends on
what you call a boyfriend.

642
01:10:03.660 --> 01:10:05.840
- I sleep with someone.
- In the village?

643
01:10:06.610 --> 01:10:08.670
- My turn.
- Okay.

644
01:10:09.300 --> 01:10:10.880
- Is it wrong?
- No.

645
01:10:11.290 --> 01:10:13.970
Outside the town.
on weekends. of course.

646
01:10:15.970 --> 01:10:19.900
You know how people are.
But remember we made a deal.

647
01:10:20.980 --> 01:10:25.130
Returning to your story. Goya.
I don't like giving advices.

648
01:10:25.970 --> 01:10:29.310
but if this was a western.
it is likely that

649
01:10:29.311 --> 01:10:31.311
the villagers wanted to lynch him
because of you.

650
01:10:32.250 --> 01:10:38.010
I know that this is not a western.
Goya. but keep in mind that

651
01:10:38.011 --> 01:10:40.011
he is much older
than you. and weaker.

652
01:10:41.320 --> 01:10:46.440
You don't have to worry.
we're through. Yes. it's finished.

653
01:10:47.070 --> 01:10:49.450
- And now you ask me why.
- Why?

654
01:10:49.950 --> 01:10:51.470
Because he doesn't do
what I command.

655
01:12:04.900 --> 01:12:07.230
Get out! Out!

656
01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:41.030
- Good morning. Cesar.
- Good morning.

657
01:12:44.260 --> 01:12:47.110
- Looks like rain. no?
- Who knows.

658
01:12:49.480 --> 01:12:53.760
I want you to tell Amparo to prepare me
a bouquet of flowers.

659
01:12:53.761 --> 01:12:54.761
As beautiful as possible.

660
01:12:57.630 --> 01:12:59.310
- Goyita?!
- What!

661
01:12:59.650 --> 01:13:02.420
- You'll be late to school!
- I'm coming.

662
01:13:03.420 --> 01:13:07.260
- You always have to be the last.
I'm going to tell your father.

663
01:13:07.261 --> 01:13:08.261
- Coming!

664
01:13:24.100 --> 01:13:26.350
- Where is my bird?

665
01:13:26.351 --> 01:13:27.351
- You stop talking of birds
and sit down to breakfast.

666
01:13:27.420 --> 01:13:29.430
- Where is my bird?
- Take your seat. I said!

667
01:13:29.630 --> 01:13:34.030
- Last night Manuel let it go.
He said they're not allowed here.

668
01:13:34.031 --> 01:13:36.031
- Gregoria. if you don't eat breakfast.
you won't go out on Sunday.

669
01:13:36.990 --> 01:13:39.720
Gregoria! Gregoria!

670
01:13:40.380 --> 01:13:43.200
It is not the question of favoritism.

671
01:13:43.850 --> 01:13:47.300
When we have to act. we act.
and it doesn't matter who is who.

672
01:13:47.500 --> 01:13:50.470
- But listen. the thing must be
investigated from all angles.

673
01:13:50.471 --> 01:13:51.471
- I'm the sergeant here!

674
01:13:52.210 --> 01:13:53.840
And stand up
when I'm speaking to you.

675
01:13:57.210 --> 01:14:00.270
And if this happens again.
you'll be transfered.

676
01:14:01.370 --> 01:14:02.690
And you know
where you belong to.

677
01:14:03.220 --> 01:14:06.250
- It's a misunderstanding...

678
01:14:06.251 --> 01:14:08.251
- I'm tired of misunderstandings
and shortcomings.

679
01:14:08.900 --> 01:14:12.930
Also you're making us look ridiculous.
It is not you I'm concerned about.

680
01:14:13.310 --> 01:14:14.880
but the prestige of the community.

681
01:14:14.881 --> 01:14:16.881
Or don't you know
what they say in the village?

682
01:14:17.080 --> 01:14:20.570
- Where is my bird?
- Gregoria!

683
01:14:20.720 --> 01:14:25.210
You see. you're an idiot. even your
own family had enough of you. Out!

684
01:14:26.070 --> 01:14:28.870
Out of here. out. out!

685
01:14:30.360 --> 01:14:33.210
- Don't get so excited...
- I'll kill you.

686
01:14:33.500 --> 01:14:36.850
- ... if a girl...
- I swear I'll kill you.

687
01:14:38.780 --> 01:14:39.650
I'll kill you.

688
01:14:59.500 --> 01:15:03.970
I'm sorry. Isabel.
You didn't deserve this.

689
01:15:17.870 --> 01:15:21.650
- Did you come to purge your guilt
or to make fun of the dead?

690
01:15:21.651 --> 01:15:22.651
- I don't know.

691
01:15:23.260 --> 01:15:27.390
Death was merciful to that child.
to let her to get rid of you.

692
01:15:28.810 --> 01:15:32.170
Have you brought flowers?
It is the first time you have.

693
01:15:36.980 --> 01:15:37.860
Take this.

694
01:15:40.630 --> 01:15:41.840
I thought it was forbidden.

695
01:15:50.460 --> 01:15:54.190
Eladio... What can I do?

696
01:15:56.070 --> 01:16:00.410
- You're too old.

697
01:16:01.940 --> 01:16:04.450
- Don't be an animal.

698
01:16:05.580 --> 01:16:07.450
She's putting you into trouble.
Alejandro.

699
01:16:09.870 --> 01:16:14.210
From the sources not worth mentioning.
I have learned that

700
01:16:14.211 --> 01:16:16.211
the family of your "girlfriend"
is aware.

701
01:16:17.320 --> 01:16:20.390
And the people in the village are
already aware of your unique romance.

702
01:16:22.370 --> 01:16:26.420
Look. there are two large groups of
opinions about you.

703
01:16:27.620 --> 01:16:31.560
The most people say
you're a little "crazy".

704
01:16:32.550 --> 01:16:36.020
To most... generous. you're wrong.

705
01:16:37.400 --> 01:16:42.270
And to some. you're a sex maniac.
and that you should be given a lesson.

706
01:16:42.271 --> 01:16:44.271
Beware of the latter group.

707
01:16:45.470 --> 01:16:49.060
- What do you think?
- That it is alright.

708
01:16:52.680 --> 01:16:59.090
Guess what? I'm living
for the first time in my life.

709
01:17:09.480 --> 01:17:11.260
And pardon me for my sincerity.
Isabel.

710
01:17:56.880 --> 01:17:59.000
- Say good night.
- Good night.

711
01:18:00.430 --> 01:18:02.320
- Hello.
- Good evening.

712
01:18:02.800 --> 01:18:07.010
Where were you?
You don't want to answer. eh?

713
01:18:09.680 --> 01:18:10.730
You ask her.

714
01:18:14.530 --> 01:18:19.750
I already know where you came from.
and you know what I mean.

715
01:18:22.450 --> 01:18:25.350
- What?!
- Nothing.

716
01:18:28.790 --> 01:18:30.020
When the truck comes?

717
01:18:31.960 --> 01:18:35.670
- On Friday.
- Then on Friday you'll go to your aunt.

718
01:18:35.671 --> 01:18:37.671
And today you won't have supper.

719
01:18:39.300 --> 01:18:42.400
Always me. right? As if you
don't have anything to say.

720
01:18:47.500 --> 01:18:48.360
Beat it.

721
01:19:05.320 --> 01:19:06.020
Lie down.

722
01:19:09.700 --> 01:19:15.690
But why? If we don't hurt anyone.
We ride a horse. we put music.

723
01:19:18.410 --> 01:19:20.140
I teach him about the birds.

724
01:19:22.300 --> 01:19:24.080
- He is very lonely.
- Lie down.

725
01:19:24.370 --> 01:19:27.240
- But don't you understand?
- Lie down! Do as I say!

726
01:19:28.540 --> 01:19:30.090
I don't care if you hit me.

727
01:20:00.950 --> 01:20:02.440
She even doesn't scream.

728
01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:07.410
Is this a starling?

729
01:20:11.040 --> 01:20:11.750
Or the finch?

730
01:20:15.350 --> 01:20:16.710
Goyita. don't bite your nails.

731
01:20:20.060 --> 01:20:24.250
Yesterday I bought the bird guide.
in Salamanca.

732
01:20:27.530 --> 01:20:29.220
Because I have to keep up
with you. right?

733
01:20:37.530 --> 01:20:41.420
- What's wrong with you?
- We will never see each other again.

734
01:20:43.270 --> 01:20:46.690
- Never again?

735
01:20:46.691 --> 01:20:48.691
- Now it's serious.
You know what today is?

736
01:20:50.300 --> 01:20:53.300
- Friday.
- I wish it didn't exist.

737
01:20:54.830 --> 01:20:59.760
- Friday. then what?
- Nothing.

738
01:21:01.380 --> 01:21:06.390
Goyita. we are both mature.
You even more than I.

739
01:21:07.960 --> 01:21:13.080
- Say what you have to say.
Don't be afraid.

740
01:21:13.081 --> 01:21:15.081
- He released the bird.
He took away your talisman.

741
01:21:16.950 --> 01:21:21.220
He won't let me do anything.

742
01:21:22.820 --> 01:21:25.110
He want me to go
to my aunt's house. forever.

743
01:21:27.460 --> 01:21:30.940
He doesn't want me
to see you again.

744
01:21:30.941 --> 01:21:33.941
He said that my father
has to be transfered. I want to kill him.

745
01:21:35.110 --> 01:21:37.600
- Whom?

746
01:21:38.960 --> 01:21:41.680
Who is he?
- The sergeant.

747
01:21:43.480 --> 01:21:49.220
You kill him. Everything is his fault.
Kill him. kill him. Kill him!

748
01:21:50.260 --> 01:21:54.920
Kill him. kill him... kill him.

749
01:21:56.710 --> 01:22:01.650
Don't say that. don't.
You can't ask for that.

750
01:22:01.651 --> 01:22:03.651
I can't kill anyone.

751
01:22:04.540 --> 01:22:08.210
Not even for you. and you are
what I mostly love in the world.

752
01:22:08.800 --> 01:22:13.030
- You don't understand.
You'll never understand.

753
01:22:14.300 --> 01:22:18.190
- For everything?
- For everything.

754
01:22:21.750 --> 01:22:23.190
You'll see. it will be okay.

755
01:22:27.610 --> 01:22:31.200
- Blackbird?
- No. Is the andarias.

756
01:23:37.390 --> 01:23:38.710
You can't live without tea.

757
01:23:44.380 --> 01:23:45.280
What a mess.

758
01:23:50.570 --> 01:23:53.090
- Shall I bring your dinner here?
- Tomorrow. tomorrow.

759
01:23:53.770 --> 01:23:55.480
Tomorrow you'll make me
a big breakfast.

760
01:23:57.940 --> 01:23:59.370
Now I'd prefer to be alone.
Amparo.

761
01:24:02.930 --> 01:24:03.640
Thank you.

762
01:24:44.610 --> 01:24:48.110
They met me in the day of success: and
I have learned by the perfect'st report.

763
01:24:48.340 --> 01:24:56.270
When I burned in desire
to question them further.

764
01:24:56.700 --> 01:25:03.470
- they made themselves air.
into which they vanished.

765
01:25:03.471 --> 01:25:04.471
- Listen. Pilar. Pilar!

766
01:25:04.930 --> 01:25:09.390
Relax. Try not to go so fast.
Macbeth!

767
01:25:09.450 --> 01:25:15.280
Try not to go so fast. I know
it's not easy to do in two weeks.

768
01:25:15.281 --> 01:25:17.281
but we need to finish the rehearsal
and it all depends on you.

769
01:25:17.340 --> 01:25:24.080
Okay? Come again. only one more time.
Go to you place!

770
01:25:25.000 --> 01:25:26.950
Come on. come on!

771
01:25:27.290 --> 01:25:34.260
The raven himself is hoarse
That croaks the fatal entrance of Duncan.

772
01:25:34.840 --> 01:25:39.670
Come. you spirits
That tend on mortal thoughts.

773
01:25:39.671 --> 01:25:41.671
unsex me here. and fill me
from the crown to the toe top-full.

774
01:25:51.720 --> 01:25:55.720
What. reading detective novels. priest?

775
01:25:57.460 --> 01:26:02.760
- Bad it was. badly finished.
- Maybe you're right.

776
01:26:04.170 --> 01:26:09.010
- Can I offer you something?
- No. I just wanted to see you.

777
01:26:09.870 --> 01:26:11.860
You and I are the same. Alejandro.

778
01:26:15.370 --> 01:26:20.850
I'm lost. priest. Nothing of what I do
makes sense.

779
01:26:22.430 --> 01:26:23.880
And I'm back to being old.

780
01:26:27.620 --> 01:26:31.160
Tomorrow the trout season begins.
we can go fishing on Sunday.

781
01:26:36.440 --> 01:26:38.010
Thanks. padre.

782
01:26:39.630 --> 01:26:43.010
It's good to have friends. down in hell.

783
01:26:48.620 --> 01:26:50.980
- What is it? Come on.
- Nothing.

784
01:26:52.010 --> 01:26:57.260
Didn't I tell you? Do you know that
I spent 5 years in the seminary?

785
01:27:05.310 --> 01:27:09.180
They wanted to make me a priest.
but luckily I escaped.

786
01:27:10.480 --> 01:27:12.250
Your colleagues were
horrible teachers.

787
01:27:17.350 --> 01:27:20.690
- What?
- I can't imagine you being a priest.

788
01:27:21.490 --> 01:27:22.580
Well. just like you.

789
01:27:25.260 --> 01:27:28.780
- Wait. wait. I remember...
- No. no.

790
01:27:29.890 --> 01:27:30.940
Pray...

791
01:27:32.930 --> 01:27:38.730
- Pray. pray sinner...
- Wait. wait.

792
01:27:39.980 --> 01:27:42.220
Now. now there is nobody around.

793
01:27:43.380 --> 01:27:50.480
- Put it on. Alexander. please.
- No. no.

794
01:27:53.350 --> 01:27:57.430
- Come on.
- No. what is this all about. Eladio?

795
01:27:57.570 --> 01:28:00.370
See what you've missed by not
graduating from the seminar.

796
01:28:04.450 --> 01:28:06.700
Now. now I'll say seriously.

797
01:28:07.410 --> 01:28:11.150
Pray. pray. you sinner...

798
01:28:12.960 --> 01:28:18.780
Oh Lord. send us a thunder...

799
01:28:20.930 --> 01:28:22.740
Okay. Okay...

800
01:28:25.910 --> 01:28:31.410
Jerusalem.
you who gave birth to prophets...

801
01:28:31.445 --> 01:28:33.411
OK let's go to Salamanca. come on!

802
01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:41.990
Lord. send us a lightning spear
and make us coal!

803
01:28:42.410 --> 01:28:46.720
Don't let these sinners
laugh at you!

804
01:29:04.170 --> 01:29:06.660
I feel old. priest.

805
01:29:09.190 --> 01:29:14.790
I've lived for nothing. and I'm not
talking about the seminar. of course.

806
01:29:18.320 --> 01:29:20.880
My wedding with the poor Isabel
had been a mistake.

807
01:29:24.520 --> 01:29:30.350
But I will say one thing. the church
of your lord won't receive a penny

808
01:29:30.351 --> 01:29:32.351
of the money from the poor Isabel.

809
01:29:33.390 --> 01:29:36.660
- Are you going to betray
the will of a deceased?

810
01:29:36.661 --> 01:29:36.695
- Yes. I do.

811
01:29:37.670 --> 01:29:43.300
- Whom are you going to leave it to then?
- You don't know yet.

812
01:29:45.720 --> 01:29:47.260
You'll be the first to know.

813
01:29:54.130 --> 01:29:55.640
I only have one friend.

814
01:30:00.060 --> 01:30:01.210
Old bastard.

815
01:30:02.460 --> 01:30:08.930
- Look. if I have ever done wrong
in my life. I regret now.

816
01:30:08.931 --> 01:30:09.931
- You?

817
01:30:12.300 --> 01:30:17.970
You can't do anything bad.
You are the kindest person I know.

818
01:30:21.980 --> 01:30:26.370
Look. let me tell you something.

819
01:30:28.830 --> 01:30:36.980
I bless you in the name of the Father.
the Son and the Holy Spirit. Amen.

820
01:30:39.460 --> 01:30:43.770
- Now. let it go.
- Thank you. padre.

821
01:30:45.810 --> 01:30:48.300
I don't believe a word
of what you say.

822
01:30:49.830 --> 01:30:53.960
- But you look very good-willed.
- Will and penance.

823
01:30:54.840 --> 01:31:01.080
Come on. You're going to Salamanca.
for five weeks. Have a good time.

824
01:31:01.081 --> 01:31:03.081
And do not come here
until you return to life.

825
01:31:03.870 --> 01:31:09.660
I have nothing to do in Salamanca...
or anywhere.

826
01:31:26.520 --> 01:31:28.940
- Where is number 17?
- There is none.

827
01:31:29.290 --> 01:31:35.740
- How can it be?
- The number 17 is number 9 now.

828
01:31:35.810 --> 01:31:39.740
- And where is 9?
- Here. in this house.

829
01:31:40.130 --> 01:31:41.520
- Thanks.
- Your welcome.

830
01:32:43.410 --> 01:32:48.800
Don Alejandro. you shouldn't have bothered.
I would send you a license.

831
01:32:48.801 --> 01:32:50.801
Or did you come for something else?

832
01:32:52.360 --> 01:32:54.890
No. I came to challenge you.

833
01:32:55.150 --> 01:32:58.690
- What?
- To challenge you. Sergeant.

834
01:33:00.530 --> 01:33:04.570
- Well. you have a good sense of humor.
- I'm serious.

835
01:33:06.970 --> 01:33:08.980
I came to challenge you to a duel.

836
01:33:13.470 --> 01:33:16.870
I think we can skip
some formalities.

837
01:33:19.060 --> 01:33:21.020
Of course you can choose a weapon.

838
01:33:25.370 --> 01:33:29.020
- Do you ever have someone
to broke your face?

839
01:33:29.021 --> 01:33:31.021
- Yes. but it's not important now.

840
01:33:31.790 --> 01:33:34.540
There is no risk for you.

841
01:33:36.410 --> 01:33:37.780
I shot really badly.

842
01:33:40.060 --> 01:33:44.340
- Whether you go away now.
or I don't know what I'll do to you.

843
01:33:44.341 --> 01:33:46.341
- You are not accepting the call?

844
01:33:47.640 --> 01:33:50.990
- Are you laughing at me?
- No.

845
01:33:52.780 --> 01:33:58.470
- Out. out. out!
- But... I have to kill you.

846
01:34:02.970 --> 01:34:07.120
- But why. Don Alejandro?
What have I done to you?

847
01:34:07.121 --> 01:34:09.121
- You would not understand.
Sergeant.

848
01:34:10.160 --> 01:34:15.080
- You are worse than I had been told.
- Sure.

849
01:34:17.830 --> 01:34:22.340
This is yours. right?
Then Keep it.

850
01:35:06.070 --> 01:35:08.450
I don't want you to go to school.

851
01:35:08.451 --> 01:35:10.451
And you shouldn't speak
with sinorita Marisa.

852
01:35:13.210 --> 01:35:16.360
Why do you have a beard?
It makes you old.

853
01:35:21.340 --> 01:35:22.280
You may kiss me.

854
01:35:28.030 --> 01:35:31.770
You are old and dirty. but
I don't want to be away from you.

855
01:35:37.750 --> 01:35:40.850
No. Neither. It is a blackbird.

856
01:37:54.710 --> 01:37:59.990
Look... it is blanks.

857
01:39:47.300 --> 01:39:50.090
Hello Alejandro. I've returned.

858
01:40:06.100 --> 01:40:12.470
Forgive me. forgive me.

859
01:40:15.180 --> 01:40:16.000
Forgive me.

860
01:40:19.790 --> 01:40:25.380
I haven't met anyone else.
And I won't meet anyone.

861
01:40:27.770 --> 01:40:28.380
Never.

862
01:40:32.450 --> 01:40:36.310
Holy fool... more than a holy fool.

863
01:40:39.720 --> 01:40:41.660
You have taught me a new word.

864
01:40:46.640 --> 01:40:49.790
No. another one.
It starts with an A.

865
01:40:54.260 --> 01:40:56.040
I'm embarrassed to tell you.

866
01:41:01.920 --> 01:41:03.030
Amor.

867
01:41:19.250 --> 01:41:22.420
We will always be together.
Forever and ever.

868
01:41:23.970 --> 01:41:26.290
And never shall we part.

869
01:41:27.220 --> 01:41:32.080
Because we have joined our blood
in this secret pact.

870
01:41:39.720 --> 01:41:43.380
For everything... forever.

871
01:41:49.730 --> 01:41:52.680
One. two. three and...

